  "doc_id": "46283",
  "text": "Gld is an important carbohydrate-metabolizing enzyme related to the glucose-trehalose conversion pathway. Disruption of the trehalose metabolism, such as from a lack of Gld, can severely affect sugar metabolism [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Though we did observe an increase in the length and the area of the eggs following Gld KD, fecundity and fertility remained unaffected. In spite of the role Gld plays in insect trehalose metabolism [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] , and possibly in insect reproduction [CITATION_6] , KD of Gld led to no marked effects in Ae. aegypti reproduction.",
